{"title_page": "Damiri Mahmud", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{More citations needed|date=January 2020}}\n}}\n\n{{short description|Indonesian writer}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Damiri Mahmud\n| occupation    = {{plainlist|\n* Writer;\n* Poet;\n* Writer for newspapers and magazines<ref>{{cite web |url=http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n2017220857.html |title=LC Name Authority File |website=Library of Congress |access-date=April 2, 2020}}</ref>}}\n| birth_date    = {{ Birth date|1945|01|17}}\n| birth_place   = [[Hamparan Perak]], [[Deli Serdang Regency]], [[North Sumatra]], [[Republic of Indonesia|Indonesia]]\n| death_date    = {{Death date and age|2019|12|30|1945|01|17}}\n| death_place   = [[Deli Serdang Regency]], [[North Sumatra]], [[Republic of Indonesia|Indonesia]]\n| nationality   = Indonesian\n| education     =  {{plainlist|\n* Ibtidaiyah, Jalan Amaliun;\n* SMEP Jalan Sindoro, [[Medan]];\n* Widyasana High School, Medan }}\n| known_for     = Poetry; Folklore adaptations<ref>{{cite web |url=http://badanbahasa.kemdikbud.go.id/lamanbahasa/node/2308 |title=Damiri Mahmud |website=Badan Pengembangan Dan Pembinaan Bahasa (Language Development and Cultivation Agency)|publisher=Kemeterian Peninikan dan Kebudayaan (Ministry of Education and Culture) |language=Indonesian |access-date=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n| notable_works = Teka-Teki; Mata; Apresiasi Puisi (Appreciation of Poetry)\n| website = {{Official URL}}\n}}\n\n'''Damiri Mahmud''' (17 January 1945 \u2013 30 December 2019) was an Indonesian writer. His writings in the form of cultural, political, and religious articles, spread in various dailies and magazines in Indonesia and Malaysia, among others: Buana News, Pelita, [[Kompas]], [[Republika (Indonesian newspaper)|Republika]], People's Thoughts, Analysis, Alert, Free, People's Mind, Lampung Post, Media Indonesia, Community Flag, Sovereign, [[Horison]], Base, Council for Literature and Daily News (Malaysia).\n\n==Career==\nHis work in the literary world of [[Medan]] began in 1969 after seven short stories were published in the magazine \"Stars, Sport, and Film\". His short stories, among others, were titled \"Ronggeng\", \"Old Bloody Old Injury Again\", and \"News from the Sea\". His short story \"Mata\" was later published in the Jakarta [[Horison]] magazine in 1970. Besides writing modern literary works, Damiri Mahmud also wrote [[folklore]]. He rewrote existing folklore with a new version. His folktale entitled \"Father's Testament\" was published by Firma Hasmar, Medan in 1976. He also received an award from the North Sumatra Library in 1978 for his folklore, entitled \"Reply to Budi\". In addition, he has also produced a novel entitled \"Teka-Teki\"<ref>{{cite book |last=Mahmud |first=Damiri |date=1988 |title=Teka\u2013teki |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=WHq-NwAACAAJ |location=Malaysia |publisher=Marwilis Publisher |isbn=9789838310154}}</ref>, published by Marwilis Publisher, [[Selangor]], Malaysia in 1988.<ref>[https://medan.tribunnews.com/2019/12/30/sastrawan-asal-sumut-damiri-mahmud-tutup-usia-sakit-paruparu-dan-sempat-masuk-rs-pirngadi Sastrawan Asal Sumut Damiri Mahmud Tutup Usia, Sakit Paruparu dan Sempat Masuk RS Pirngadi] {{in lang|id}}</ref>\n\n== Works ==\n\n* ''Wasiat Ayah'' Firma Hasmar, Medan (1976)\n* ''Membalas Budi'' (1978)\n* ''Titian Laut I'' Language and Literature Council, Kuala Lumpur (1982)\n* ''Muara Satu'' (1984)\n* ''Nafas Islam dalam Sastra Indonesia'' (1984)\n* ''Titian Laut II'' Language and Literature Council, Kuala Lumpur (1986)\n* ''Teka-Teki'' Marwilis Publisher, Malaysia (1988)\n* ''Muara Dua'' Firma Maju Medan (1989)\n* ''Titian Laut III'' Language and Literature Council, Kuala Lumpur (1991)\n* ''Damai di Bumi: Kumpulan Sajak'' Deparsenibud, North Sumatra (2000)\n* ''Tonggak''\n* ''Bosnia Kita''\n* ''Kontroversi Al-Quran Berwajah Puisi''\n* ''Esensi dan Dinamika''\n* ''Perisa''\n* ''Ensiklopedia Sejarah dan Kebudayaan Melayu''\n* ''Daun-daun Sejarah'' (2000)\n* ''Beri Kami Satu Bentuk Hidup Bersahaja'' (2000)\n* ''Apresiasi puisi: suara kepenyairan sastrawan Medan'' (2012)<ref>{{cite book |last=Mahmud |first=Damiri |date=2012 |title=Apresiasi puisi: suara kepenyairan sastrawan Medan |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=HY5fMwEACAAJ |location=Indonesia |isbn=9786022450085}}</ref>\n* ''Menafsir Kembali Amir Hamzah'' North Sumatra Library Board, 2013 and Ombak (2017)\n* ''Rumah Tersembunyi Chairil Anwar'' Unimed Press (2014) and Ombak (2018)\n* ''Patung'' Badan Perpustakaan Sumatera Utara (2018)\n* ''Halakah Panggang'' Obelia Publisher (2018)\n* ''Menjadi Tanah'' Obelia Publisher (2019)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mahmud, Damiri}}\n[[Category:1945 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:Indonesian writers]]\n\n\n{{Indonesia-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{More citations needed|date=January 2020}}\n}}\n\n{{short description|Indonesian writer}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Damiri Mahmud\n| occupation    = {{plainlist|\n* Writer;\n* Writer for newspapers and magazines<ref>{{cite web |url=http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n2017220857.html |title=LC Name Authority File |website=Library of Congress |access-date=April 2, 2020}}</ref>}}\n| birth_date    = {{ Birth date|1945|01|17}}\n| birth_place   = [[Hamparan Perak]], [[Deli Serdang Regency]], [[North Sumatra]], [[Republic of Indonesia|Indonesia]]\n| death_date    = {{Death date and age|2019|12|30|1945|01|17}}\n| death_place   = [[Deli Serdang Regency]], [[North Sumatra]], [[Republic of Indonesia|Indonesia]]\n| nationality   = Indonesian\n| education     =  {{plainlist|\n* Ibtidaiyah, Jalan Amaliun;\n* SMEP Jalan Sindoro, [[Medan]];\n* Widyasana High School, Medan }}\n| known_for     = Poetry; Folklore adaptations<ref>{{cite web |url=http://badanbahasa.kemdikbud.go.id/lamanbahasa/node/2308 |title=Damiri Mahmud |website=Badan Pengembangan Dan Pembinaan Bahasa (Language Development and Cultivation Agency)|publisher=Kemeterian Peninikan dan Kebudayaan (Ministry of Education and Culture) |language=Indonesian |access-date=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n| notable_works = Teka-Teki; Mata; Apresiasi Puisi (Appreciation of Poetry)\n| website = {{Official URL}}\n}}\n\n'''Damiri Mahmud''' (17 January 1945 \u2013 30 December 2019) was an Indonesian writer. His writings in the form of cultural, political, and religious articles, spread in various dailies and magazines in Indonesia and Malaysia, among others: Buana News, Pelita, [[Kompas]], [[Republika (Indonesian newspaper)|Republika]], People's Thoughts, Analysis, Alert, Free, People's Mind, Lampung Post, Media Indonesia, Community Flag, Sovereign, [[Horison]], Base, Council for Literature and Daily News (Malaysia).\n\n==Career==\nHis work in the literary world of [[Medan]] began in 1969 after seven short stories were published in the magazine \"Stars, Sport, and Film\". His short stories, among others, were titled \"Ronggeng\", \"Old Bloody Old Injury Again\", and \"News from the Sea\". His short story \"Mata\" was later published in the Jakarta [[Horison]] magazine in 1970. Besides writing modern literary works, Damiri Mahmud also wrote [[folklore]]. He rewrote existing folklore with a new version. His folktale entitled \"Father's Testament\" was published by Firma Hasmar, Medan in 1976. He also received an award from the North Sumatra Library in 1978 for his folklore, entitled \"Reply to Budi\". In addition, he has also produced a novel entitled \"Teka-Teki\"<ref>{{cite book |last=Mahmud |first=Damiri |date=1988 |title=Teka\u2013teki |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=WHq-NwAACAAJ |location=Malaysia |publisher=Marwilis Publisher |isbn=9789838310154}}</ref>, published by Marwilis Publisher, [[Selangor]], Malaysia in 1988.<ref>[https://medan.tribunnews.com/2019/12/30/sastrawan-asal-sumut-damiri-mahmud-tutup-usia-sakit-paruparu-dan-sempat-masuk-rs-pirngadi Sastrawan Asal Sumut Damiri Mahmud Tutup Usia, Sakit Paruparu dan Sempat Masuk RS Pirngadi] {{in lang|id}}</ref>\n\n== Works ==\n\n* ''Wasiat Ayah'' Firma Hasmar, Medan (1976)\n* ''Membalas Budi'' (1978)\n* ''Titian Laut I'' Language and Literature Council, Kuala Lumpur (1982)\n* ''Muara Satu'' (1984)\n* ''Nafas Islam dalam Sastra Indonesia'' (1984)\n* ''Titian Laut II'' Language and Literature Council, Kuala Lumpur (1986)\n* ''Teka-Teki'' Marwilis Publisher, Malaysia (1988)\n* ''Muara Dua'' Firma Maju Medan (1989)\n* ''Titian Laut III'' Language and Literature Council, Kuala Lumpur (1991)\n* ''Damai di Bumi: Kumpulan Sajak'' Deparsenibud, North Sumatra (2000)\n* ''Tonggak''\n* ''Bosnia Kita''\n* ''Kontroversi Al-Quran Berwajah Puisi''\n* ''Esensi dan Dinamika''\n* ''Perisa''\n* ''Ensiklopedia Sejarah dan Kebudayaan Melayu''\n* ''Daun-daun Sejarah'' (2000)\n* ''Beri Kami Satu Bentuk Hidup Bersahaja'' (2000)\n* ''Apresiasi puisi: suara kepenyairan sastrawan Medan'' (2012)<ref>{{cite book |last=Mahmud |first=Damiri |date=2012 |title=Apresiasi puisi: suara kepenyairan sastrawan Medan |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=HY5fMwEACAAJ |location=Indonesia |isbn=9786022450085}}</ref>\n* ''Menafsir Kembali Amir Hamzah'' North Sumatra Library Board, 2013 and Ombak (2017)\n* ''Rumah Tersembunyi Chairil Anwar'' Unimed Press (2014) and Ombak (2018)\n* ''Patung'' Badan Perpustakaan Sumatera Utara (2018)\n* ''Halakah Panggang'' Obelia Publisher (2018)\n* ''Menjadi Tanah'' Obelia Publisher (2019)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mahmud, Damiri}}\n[[Category:1945 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:Indonesian writers]]\n\n\n{{Indonesia-writer-stub}}\n", "name_user": "SpookiePuppy", "label": "safe", "comment": "Infobox: Occupation parameter: adding \"Poet\"", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Damiri_Mahmud"}
{"title_page": "Kon Saab..?", "text_new": "{{short description|Hindi short film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| image                    =  Kon saab.jpg\n| caption                  =  Poster\n| genre                    = \n| based_on                 = \n| director                 = Mukul Sharma\n| starring                 = Tarun Kapur<br>Himanshu Pandey<br>Ramkishan gujjar<br>Sanjay Tripathi<br>Sahil Patel\n| writer                   = mukul Sharma \n| theme_music_composer     = \n| composer                 = \n| country                  = [[India]]\n| language                 = [[English language|English]], [[Hindi]]\n| location                 = \n| cinematography           = Azain Khan \n| editor                   = \n| network                  = \n| picture_format           = \n| released                 = \n| first_aired              = \n| last_aired               = \n| company                  = \n| distributor              = Lucky Commando Films\n| executive_producer       = \n| runtime                  = 25 minutes\n| producer                 = Lucky Bisht\n| num_seasons              = \n| num_episodes             = \n| list_episodes            = \n| music                    = Haston\n| website                  = \n| related                  = \n}}\n\n'''''Kon Saab..?''''' is a 2019 [[Bollywood]] suspense thriller comedy and drama short movie Produced by Lucky Commando Films.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u2018Kaun Saab..? Short Movie Produced by Lucky commando films.. |url=http://bollywoodkhabar.in/kon-saab-short-movie-produced-by-lucky-commando-films/ |website=bollywoodkhabar |language=en |date=31 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Lucky Commando films Produced by \u2018Kaun Saab..? Short Movie. |url=http://thebollywoodtadka.com/index.php/2020/03/31/lucky-commando-films-produced-kon-saab-short-movie/ |website=Thebollywoodtadka |language=en |date=31 March 2020}}</ref> Producer Lucky Bisht Director & written by Mukul Sharma. starting trun Kapur and ramkishan gujjar and lead role Himanshu Pandey & Sanjay tripathi.<ref>{{cite web |title=kon Saab..?Short film questions VIP treatment given to terrorists in jail |url=http://www.canindia.com/short-film-questions-vip-treatment-given-to-terrorists-in-jail/ |website=canindian |language=en |date=12 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=kon Saab..?Short film questions VIP treatment given to terrorists in jail |url=https://www.britishasianews.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=34837 |website=bristisasia |language=en |date=12 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\n\n''Kon Saab..?'' A short film questioning [[VIP]] treatment given to [[terrorists]] in [[jail]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\u2018Kaun Saab\u2019: A short film questioning VIP treatment given to terrorists in jail\n |url=https://www.nationalheraldindia.com/films/kaun-saab-a-short-film-questioning-vip-treatment-given-to-terrorists-in-jail |website=Nationalheralindia |language=en |date=12 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u2018Kaun Saab\u2019: A short film questioning VIP treatment given to terrorists in jail\n |url=https://zeenews.india.com/bollywood/short-film-kaun-saab-questions-vip-treatment-given-to-terrorists-in-jail-2179549.html |website=Zeenews |language=en |date=12 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Challenges faced by police\n |url=https://telanganatoday.com/challenges-faced-by-police |website=telanganatoday |language=en |date=12 February 2019}}</ref>\nThe film focuses on the challenges being faced by police personnel in police stations as a big amount is being spent on insignificant things but basic facilities have still a long way to go.Lucky Bisht, the ex-commando, has produced the short film along with Kashwi Productions. A satire, the film brings several challenges being combated by police personnel and highlights their plight.<ref>{{cite web |title=Short film questions VIP treatment given to terrorists in jail |url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=561392 |website=daijiworld |language=en |date=12 February 2019}}</ref> Explaining the film's title, Bisht said, \"The film features a back-to-back fleet of cars running on roads which stuns people around. Out of inquisitiveness, they ask if any VIP is coming in their city. They exchange their query saying Kaun saab (Who is it?) and get to know that it is a terrorist who is going to jail, escorted by a huge police convoy. Hence, the name Kaun Saab.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=\u2018Kaun Saab\u2019: The film focuses on the challenges being faced by police personnel in police stations as a big amount is being spent on insignificant things but basic facilities have still a long way to go\n |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/short-film-questions-vip-treatment-given-to-terrorists-in-jail/1477214 |website=Outlook |language=en |date=12 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Short film 'Kaun Saab' questions VIP treatment given to terrorists in jail |url=http://www.indianews-today.com/news/short-film-039kaun-saab039-questions-vip-treatment-given-to-terrorists-in-jail|website=indianews |language=en |date=12 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Short film questions VIP treatment given to terrorists in jail |url=http://www.theweekendleader.com/Headlines/21690/short-film-questions-vip-treatment-given-to-terrorists-in-jail.html |website=theweekendleader |language=en |date=12 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n\n* Tarun Kapur as Cop\n* Ram kishan gujjar as Cop\n* Sanjay Tripathi as Thief\n* Himanshu Pandey as Thief\n* Sahil Patel as thief\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{imdb title|9768954}}\n*{{YouTube|id=wrUtWefto0A|title=Kon Saab..?}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Indian thriller films]]\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Hindi short film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| image                    =  Kon saab.jpg\n| caption                  =  Poster\n| genre                    = \n| based_on                 = \n| director                 = Mukul Sharma\n| starring                 = Tarun Kapur<br>Himanshu Pandey<br>Ramkishan gujjar<br>Sanjay Tripathi<br>Sahil Patel\n| writer                   = mukul Sharma \n| theme_music_composer     = \n| composer                 = \n| country                  = [[India]]\n| language                 = [[English language|English]], [[Hindi]]\n| location                 = \n| cinematography           = Azain Khan \n| editor                   = \n| network                  = \n| picture_format           = \n| released                 = \n| first_aired              = \n| last_aired               = \n| company                  = \n| distributor              = Lucky Commando Films\n| executive_producer       = \n| runtime                  = 25 minutes\n| producer                 = Lucky Bisht\n| num_seasons              = \n| num_episodes             = \n| list_episodes            = \n| music                    = Haston\n| website                  = \n| related                  = \n}}\n\n'''''Kon Saab..?''''' is a 2019 [[Bollywood]] suspense thriller comedy and drama short movie Produced by Lucky Commando Films<ref>{{cite web |title=\u2018Kaun Saab..? Short Movie Produced by Lucky commando films.. |url=http://bollywoodkhabar.in/kon-saab-short-movie-produced-by-lucky-commando-films/ |website=bollywoodkhabar |language=en |date=31 March 2020}}</ref>.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lucky Commando films Produced by \u2018Kaun Saab..? Short Movie. |url=http://thebollywoodtadka.com/index.php/2020/03/31/lucky-commando-films-produced-kon-saab-short-movie/ |website=Thebollywoodtadka |language=en |date=31 March 2020}}</ref> Producer Lucky Bisht Director & written by Mukul Sharma. starting trun Kapur and ramkishan gujjar and lead role Himanshu Pandey & Sanjay tripathi.<ref>{{cite web |title=kon Saab..?Short film questi